<h1>Webhooks</h1>
<p class="lede">
  Configure a default webhook for your account and choose how Meerkat shapes JSON payloads.
  Per-task overrides are still supported via the Tasks API.
</p>

<h2 class="dash-section-title">Default webhook</h2>
<p>
  Save a default endpoint and optional headers. When creating tasks, set
  <code>output_webhook</code> to <code>default</code> (or omit it if a default is configured)
  to deliver results here.
</p>

<%= form_with url: docs_webhook_settings_path, scope: :webhook_settings, class: "dash-form" do |f| %>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :default_output_webhook, "Webhook URL", class: "form-label" %>
    <%= f.url_field :default_output_webhook,
      value: current_customer.default_output_webhook,
      placeholder: "https://your-app.com/hooks/meerkat",
      class: "form-input" %>
  </div>

  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :default_webhook_headers_json, "Optional headers (JSON)", class: "form-label" %>
    <%= f.text_area :default_webhook_headers_json,
      rows: 6,
      class: "form-input",
      value: current_customer.default_webhook_headers_json,
      placeholder: '{ "Authorization": "Bearer sk_live_..." }' %>
    <p class="field-hint">Applied only when a task uses <code>output_webhook: "default"</code>.</p>
  </div>

  <%= f.submit "Save default webhook", class: "btn btn-primary" %>
<% end %>

<% if current_customer.default_webhook_configured? %>
  <div class="key-banner" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
    <p><strong style="color:var(--accent)">Default webhook active</strong></p>
    <p style="color:var(--muted);margin:0"><code><%= current_customer.default_output_webhook %></code></p>
  </div>
<% end %>

<h2 class="dash-section-title">Using default vs custom webhooks</h2>
<pre class="api-code"><code>{
  "task": {
    "description": "Monitor package tracking",
    "input_params": { "courier_tracking_link": "https://..." },
    "output_webhook": "default"
  }
}</code></pre>

<p>Or pass a full URL to override for a single task:</p>
<pre class="api-code"><code>{
  "task": {
    "description": "...",
    "input_params": { },
    "output_webhook": "https://your-app.com/hooks/meerkat"
  }
}</code></pre>

<h2 class="dash-section-title">Default output format</h2>
<p>If you omit <code>output_format</code>, Meerkat uses the <code>default</code> preset:</p>
<pre class="api-code"><code>{
  "event": "run_completed",
  "task_id": 1,
  "task_run_id": 42,
  "occurred_at": "2026-06-20T12:00:00Z",
  "data": {
    "summary": "...",
    "findings": { },
    "change_detected": true
  }
}</code></pre>

<h2 class="dash-section-title">Other output formats</h2>
<p>Optional — pass <code>output_format</code> on task create to reshape the webhook payload.</p>
<div class="endpoint"><span class="method method-get">default</span> Standard envelope with <code>data</code> object (used when omitted)</div>
<div class="endpoint"><span class="method method-get">compact</span> <code>summary</code>, <code>change_detected</code>, <code>findings</code> at top level</div>
<div class="endpoint"><span class="method method-get">flat</span> Findings merged into webhook root alongside metadata</div>
<div class="endpoint"><span class="method method-get">findings_only</span> Findings object only</div>
<div class="endpoint"><span class="method method-get">minimal</span> <code>event</code>, <code>task_id</code>, <code>summary</code>, <code>change_detected</code></div>

<h2 class="dash-section-title">Delivery headers</h2>
<p>Every delivery includes:</p>
<ul style="color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:1rem;padding-left:1.25rem">
  <li><code>Content-Type: application/json</code></li>
  <li><code>User-Agent: Meerkat/1.0</code></li>
  <li><code>X-Meerkat-Event</code> — event type (e.g. <code>run_completed</code>)</li>
</ul>
<p>Your default webhook headers are merged on top when using <code>output_webhook: "default"</code>.</p>

<h2 class="dash-section-title">Retries</h2>
<p>Failed deliveries are retried with backoff. Inspect delivery history on a task's <strong>Webhook events</strong> tab or via <code>GET /tasks/:id/events</code>.</p>

<p class="api-footer-links">
  <%= link_to "Tasks dashboard →", docs_dashboard_tasks_path %>
  · <%= link_to "Tasks API →", docs_section_path("tasks") %>
</p>
